  <p><strong>A small car causing a small problem</strong> </p>
  <p>Helsingin Sanomat 26.11.2001, .Weird event. .column, a story by Tuija  Sairio</p>
  <p>
  </p>
  <p>Back in 1960s. I was on a local bus coming from Puistola and headed for  Helsinki city center. It was a bright summer day. The bus stopped by the Malmi  cemetery to pick up a passenger. Just when it was leaving the bus stop there  was a thump.</p>
  <p>
  </p>
  <p>A small car had started from a company yard on our right and has  clashed to the front bumper of our bus.</p>
  <p>
  </p>
  <p>The bus stopped and the bus driver, a tall and sturdy man, stood up  calmly, pulled the front door open, and said to the small car.s driver: .The  pram should be lifted in through the back-door.. After a brief clearing the  driver came back in, straightened his cap and the travel continued.</p>
